  <description><![CDATA[<p>If you are looking for a convenient hotel close to the slopes, look no further than Hotel Cà Fiore. The Campo Smith lift is just 200 metres away, so you can be on the mountain in no time at all. The hotel itself is popular with British guests who love the fact the staff go out of their way to ensure everyone has a great holiday. The décor throughout is a typical mountain style with natural woods and nice open spaces, inside and out. We particularly love the fireplace in the restaurant and on a warn sunny afternoon, the terrace is a great place to sit back and enjoy some après drinks.  </p>
<p>The centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/632726451b0d4569b6f2cd0d56b628c3" href="/{localLink:umb://document/632726451b0d4569b6f2cd0d56b628c3}" title="Bardonecchia">Bardonecchia</a> is about 700 metres from the hotel and a nice stroll to help stretch out the legs. After exploring the shops, restaurants and bars, if you don't have the energy to do the walk home, you can always jump on the resort bus which does the rounds.  </p>
<p>The hotel has its own wellness area equipped with a sauna and three relaxing whirlpools, perfect if you need a bit of chill time. Don't get too comfy however as you certainly don't want to miss out on your four course evening meal severed up in the hotels lovely restaurant. Once suitably stuffed you can retire to the bar for a few drinks before settling down for the evening in one of the 34 hotel guest rooms. </p>
<p><span>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 30 mins by coach from Turin airport.</span></p>]]></description>
